WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.903 --> 00:00:06.431
Getting rid of the Mark unleashed a
force on this world that could destroy it.

2
00:00:07.841 --> 00:00:09.561
This is The Darkness.
right? It's got to be.

3
00:00:09.676 --> 00:00:11.876
So. what. she shows up and
everybody goes <i>28 Days Later?</i>

4
00:00:11.945 --> 00:00:13.846
They were like rabid
dogs. they didn't stop

5
00:00:14.448 --> 00:00:15.568
<i>Maybe it was the smoke.</i>

6
00:00:15.749 --> 00:00:17.547
Anybody who was
outside. they were exposed.

7
00:00:17.751 --> 00:00:19.591
<i>- That wasn't human.</i>
- Why not? I killed Death.

8
00:00:19.853 --> 00:00:21.549
<i>I'm pretty much
open for anything.</i>

9
00:00:22.623 --> 00:00:23.863
- They bleed on you?
- They did.

10
00:00:23.991 --> 00:00:25.751
- It might be transmittable.
<i>- I'll go.</i>

11
00:00:25.792 --> 00:00:27.192
<i>And you save my baby girl.</i>

12
00:00:27.361 --> 00:00:28.659
<i>Her name is Amara.</i>

13
00:00:30.564 --> 00:00:32.260
Look. we can just
wait for them to die.

14
00:00:32.533 --> 00:00:34.533
We can't save Cass if
we're stuck in some hospital.

15
00:00:34.701 --> 00:00:36.101
<i>I can't help myself.</i>

16
00:00:37.271 --> 00:00:38.603
He's still alive.

17
00:00:38.839 --> 00:00:40.808
Brothers. Save me
from doing worse.

18
00:00:44.444 --> 00:00:45.605
All right. let's gear up.

19
00:00:46.513 --> 00:00:49.347
Saving people means
all of the people.

20
00:00:49.516 --> 00:00:52.213
- What are you thinking?
- Get Jenna and the baby somewhere safe.

21
00:00:52.653 --> 00:00:53.848
Without a shot?

22
00:00:55.122 --> 00:00:56.146
Hey!

23
00:01:00.294 --> 00:01:01.318
<i>Hey. you good?</i>

24
00:01:01.562 --> 00:01:03.106
Yeah. I'm gonna run Jenna
up to her grandmother's.

25
00:01:03.130 --> 00:01:04.154
<i>What about you? You okay?</i>

26
00:01:04.331 --> 00:01:06.851
- Like it or not. I'm gonna find a cure.
- Yeah. I know you are.

27
00:02:19.940 --> 00:02:21.772
<i>H-A-T-E.</i>

28
00:02:22.409 --> 00:02:25.140
<i>It was with this left hand that
old brother Cain struck the blow</i>

29
00:02:25.379 --> 00:02:27.007
<i>that laid his brother low.</i>

30
00:02:27.180 --> 00:02:28.705
<i>L-O-V-E.</i>

31
00:02:29.416 --> 00:02:30.936
<i>You see these
fingers? They're arched.</i>

32
00:02:31.051 --> 00:02:34.044
<i>These fingers have veins that
run straight to the soul of man.</i>

33
00:02:34.354 --> 00:02:36.516
<i>The right hand.
friends. the hand of love.</i>

34
00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:39.558
<i>Now watch and I'll
show you the story of life.</i>

35
00:02:40.027 --> 00:02:42.826
<i>These fingers. dear hearts. is
always a-warrin' and a-tuggin'.</i>

36
00:02:43.030 --> 00:02:44.931
<i>one against the other.</i>

37
00:02:45.165 --> 00:02:46.189
<i>Now watch 'em.</i>

38
00:02:47.200 --> 00:02:50.500
<i>Old brother left hand.
left hand hates a-fightin'.</i>

39
00:02:50.737 --> 00:02:52.782
<i>- Can you talk?
- And it looks like love's a goner.</i>

40
00:02:52.806 --> 00:02:54.646
- Or are you too far gone?
<i>- But wait a minute.</i>

41
00:02:55.142 --> 00:02:56.542
- What?
<i>- Wait a minute.</i>

42
00:02:56.810 --> 00:02:58.438
<i>Hot dog! Love's a-winnin'.</i>

43
00:02:58.879 --> 00:03:00.848
<i>Yes. siree. It's
love that's won.</i>

44
00:03:01.515 --> 00:03:03.848
<i>And old left-hand hate
is down for the count.</i>

45
00:03:04.184 --> 00:03:05.345
Good answer.

46
00:03:31.311 --> 00:03:34.975
- Nice neighborhood.
- Yeah. I pretty much grew up here.

47
00:03:35.916 --> 00:03:37.578
Learned to ride my
bike down the road.

48
00:03:37.884 --> 00:03:40.217
Had my first kiss in that
blue house over there.

49
00:03:41.088 --> 00:03:42.852
Lost my virginity up there.

50
00:03:43.423 --> 00:03:45.858
- I'll bet blue house was pissed.
- She was.

51
00:03:46.359 --> 00:03:47.759
- Do you mind?
- Yeah.

52
00:03:50.330 --> 00:03:52.629
Hey. beautiful.

53
00:03:53.934 --> 00:03:57.029
Anyway. that's why I
asked you to bring us here.

54
00:03:57.504 --> 00:04:00.633
After everything that
happened. it just feels safe.

55
00:04:01.575 --> 00:04:02.941
Well. good. Safe is good.

56
00:04:05.245 --> 00:04:07.845
- You're so great with her.
- Well. what can I say? Chicks dig me.

57
00:04:09.349 --> 00:04:11.784
- Well. look. I should...
- Right. Sure.

58
00:04:15.188 --> 00:04:17.054
You're gonna be
okay. Both of you.

59
00:04:17.758 --> 00:04:21.354
I know. What about you? And
Sam? Are you gonna be okay?

60
00:04:21.962 --> 00:04:23.897
Well. for us the
bar's pretty low.

61
00:04:26.366 --> 00:04:27.366
See ya.

62
00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:33.039
Dean? Thank you. For everything.

63
00:04:40.046 --> 00:04:41.878
- Jenna.
- Hi. Grandma.

64
00:04:50.457 --> 00:04:52.949
After you called. they did
a big report on the news.

65
00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:55.391
That weatherman I don't
like. with the big teeth.

66
00:04:55.762 --> 00:04:58.254
he said some kind of
freak storm hit Superior.

67
00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:02.133
Yeah. it was crazy.

68
00:05:02.369 --> 00:05:03.393
Well. don't you worry.

69
00:05:03.770 --> 00:05:05.796
If that thing rolls our
way. I've got a generator.

70
00:05:06.106 --> 00:05:08.666
and enough canned green
beans to last 'til Judgment Day.

71
00:05:08.842 --> 00:05:09.842
Good to know.

72
00:05:10.877 --> 00:05:13.108
And this must be Amara.

73
00:05:13.713 --> 00:05:16.547
Oh. What a little angel.

74
00:05:17.050 --> 00:05:18.848
Yep. She's a miracle.

75
00:05:19.586 --> 00:05:20.849
And her folks?

76
00:05:28.728 --> 00:05:29.855
It's a long story.

77
00:05:30.697 --> 00:05:32.308
Well. then it can
wait till after your nap.

78
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:34.597
- My what?
- When's the last time you slept?

79
00:05:34.968 --> 00:05:37.267
Because. and I mean this
in the nicest possible way.

80
00:05:37.470 --> 00:05:39.063
you look like poop on parade.

81
00:05:39.272 --> 00:05:40.900
Now. I made up
the guest bedroom.

82
00:05:41.174 --> 00:05:43.143
and I got your father's
old crib out for the baby.

83
00:05:43.376 --> 00:05:44.844
So. I will put her down.

84
00:05:45.278 --> 00:05:50.080
Yes. I will. While you go
upstairs and have a rest. all right?

85
00:05:50.650 --> 00:05:53.085
Honestly. a nap sounds
awesome right now.

86
00:05:53.386 --> 00:05:55.582
Well. then. you just
go right upstairs. missy.

87
00:05:56.089 --> 00:05:57.148
Thank you.

88
00:06:00.126 --> 00:06:01.560
Who's the little angel?

89
00:06:03.096 --> 00:06:04.860
No. you have to go to sleep.

90
00:06:05.332 --> 00:06:08.496
Who's a beautiful
angel? You are.

91
00:06:08.768 --> 00:06:10.498
Beautiful. Here we go.

92
00:06:12.739 --> 00:06:14.367
Here we go.

93
00:06:17.043 --> 00:06:19.410
Night. night. doodlebug.

94
00:07:27.247 --> 00:07:28.271
What's your name?

95
00:07:29.816 --> 00:07:31.045
Bite me.

96
00:07:35.121 --> 00:07:36.453
Okay. Bite Me.

97
00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:38.823
How long have you been infected?

98
00:07:40.327 --> 00:07:41.761
Could ask you the same thing.

99
00:07:43.330 --> 00:07:44.423
We smell our own.

100
00:07:45.265 --> 00:07:47.097
- Answer the question.
- Why?

101
00:07:49.102 --> 00:07:50.782
You wanna know how
much time you got left?

102
00:07:52.806 --> 00:07:53.865
I wanna know everything.

103
00:07:55.141 --> 00:07:56.302
Mmm-hmm.

104
00:07:58.178 --> 00:07:59.178
What's in it for me?

105
00:08:01.181 --> 00:08:03.673
- Well. if I can find a cure...
- "If."

106
00:08:07.220 --> 00:08:08.745
I want something real.

107
00:08:12.325 --> 00:08:14.123
Something I can
hold in my hands.

108
00:08:14.794 --> 00:08:15.794
Like what?

109
00:08:20.700 --> 00:08:21.700
Your pudding.

110
00:08:40.954 --> 00:08:43.753
I was infected last night. You?

111
00:08:44.691 --> 00:08:45.691
This morning.

112
00:08:47.827 --> 00:08:49.921
- Wait. a second. then why...
- Am I further along?

113
00:08:50.463 --> 00:08:51.463
Don't know.

114
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:54.763
This thing. it ain't math.

115
00:08:56.236 --> 00:08:59.798
I seen some people change
fast. some change slow.

116
00:09:01.274 --> 00:09:02.799
But in the end.

117
00:09:03.977 --> 00:09:05.502
we all end up the same.

118
00:09:06.546 --> 00:09:07.809
We go psycho.

119
00:09:09.749 --> 00:09:11.115
Then we go boom.

120
00:09:14.988 --> 00:09:16.081
Well. that's not...

121
00:09:19.692 --> 00:09:20.887
I'm gonna fix this.

122
00:09:22.128 --> 00:09:23.187
Liar!

123
00:09:25.965 --> 00:09:27.331
You and me.

124
00:09:28.068 --> 00:09:29.263
we're dead.

125
00:09:32.572 --> 00:09:34.473
We're just taking our
sweet time about it.

126
00:09:38.178 --> 00:09:39.476
So. if you were smart.

127
00:09:41.214 --> 00:09:42.682
you'd put a bullet in me.

128
00:09:46.386 --> 00:09:47.945
Then eat one yourself.

129
00:10:02.202 --> 00:10:03.465
Come on. Cass.

130
00:10:07.974 --> 00:10:08.974
Hmm.

131
00:10:10.143 --> 00:10:12.237
- Dean.
- As in Winchester?

132
00:10:13.880 --> 00:10:17.044
Probably. Do the honors.

133
00:10:23.356 --> 00:10:26.121
Good morning. handsome.

134
00:10:27.360 --> 00:10:29.955
Efram? Jonah?

135
00:10:31.397 --> 00:10:32.831
What's happening?

136
00:10:33.099 --> 00:10:35.193
We have questions
for you. Castiel.

137
00:10:37.070 --> 00:10:38.265
Why am I...

138
00:10:38.938 --> 00:10:41.533
- I asked for help.
- And I asked for a vessel

139
00:10:41.741 --> 00:10:45.041
that didn't have
psoriasis. Crap happens.

140
00:10:46.546 --> 00:10:49.311
- No.
- No what?

141
00:10:50.683 --> 00:10:55.553
No. you don't
understand. I'm cursed.

142
00:10:56.623 --> 00:10:57.852
You should run.

143
00:11:22.849 --> 00:11:26.684
Did you hear that?
Sounded like raccoons.

144
00:11:28.421 --> 00:11:29.684
That was not a raccoon.

145
00:12:05.592 --> 00:12:07.060
Jenna. don't!

146
00:12:08.661 --> 00:12:10.527
Jenna. No!

147
00:12:11.097 --> 00:12:13.362
- The Devil's in that girl.
- What?

148
00:12:13.866 --> 00:12:15.858
- I'm calling Father Wyatt.
- Grandma. no.

149
00:12:16.569 --> 00:12:17.935
Well. who are we gonna call?

150
00:12:18.538 --> 00:12:19.538
Ghostbusters.

151
00:12:21.040 --> 00:12:24.477
Jenna. hey. Whoa. whoa.
whoa. Slow down. What's wrong?

152
00:12:37.624 --> 00:12:40.355
I mean. it sounds like
something out of <i>The Exorcist.</i>

153
00:12:40.994 --> 00:12:43.154
- That's what I said.
<i>- So. you're thinking demon?</i>

154
00:12:43.263 --> 00:12:45.562
Or the kid got infected
by something. you know.

155
00:12:45.732 --> 00:12:48.031
Who knows what was
in that giant. crazy fart.

156
00:12:48.401 --> 00:12:50.393
Wow.

157
00:12:51.404 --> 00:12:52.565
Vivid. Thanks.

158
00:12:53.106 --> 00:12:55.586
<i>- Look. man. I know you're flying solo...</i>
- No. I'm fine. Dean.

159
00:12:55.642 --> 00:12:57.668
Look. don't worry
about me and just...

160
00:12:59.078 --> 00:13:01.638
Just help Jenna. And if you
need anything then call me.

161
00:13:02.715 --> 00:13:05.184
Will do. How you doing?
How's Zombieland?

162
00:13:08.054 --> 00:13:11.115
It's good. It's great.

163
00:13:16.963 --> 00:13:18.261
Where's Metatron?

164
00:13:22.168 --> 00:13:23.329
I don't know.

165
00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:31.835
- Where's Metatron. Castiel?
- Mercy. brother. please.

166
00:13:32.545 --> 00:13:34.571
"Brother"?

167
00:13:38.584 --> 00:13:39.882
What are you?

168
00:13:43.022 --> 00:13:44.513
I'm an angel of the Lord.

169
00:13:45.458 --> 00:13:46.619
That so?

170
00:13:47.360 --> 00:13:51.889
'Cause near as I can tell. when
you have to choose between Heaven

171
00:13:52.498 --> 00:13:54.899
- and the Winchesters...
- You choose them.

172
00:13:55.335 --> 00:13:56.803
Every time.

173
00:13:58.204 --> 00:14:00.537
So. see. you're not my brother.

174
00:14:01.841 --> 00:14:03.275
And if I had it my way.

175
00:14:04.243 --> 00:14:05.472
I'd take this blade.

176
00:14:06.312 --> 00:14:08.611
stick it in your heart...

177
00:14:08.848 --> 00:14:12.808
and call that a damn good day.

178
00:14:15.355 --> 00:14:16.755
Then do it.

179
00:14:27.367 --> 00:14:28.801
Fun's just getting started.

180
00:15:33.032 --> 00:15:34.032
Hey. Sam.

181
00:15:35.902 --> 00:15:36.995
How do you know my name?

182
00:15:38.671 --> 00:15:40.367
- Who are you?
- Mmm.

183
00:15:41.207 --> 00:15:42.869
Think you mean "what."

184
00:15:45.978 --> 00:15:50.109
Here's a hint. you and your brother.
been real good for business lately.

185
00:15:53.519 --> 00:15:56.284
- You're a reaper.
- Circle gets the square.

186
00:15:57.423 --> 00:15:58.423
What's your name?

187
00:16:00.259 --> 00:16:01.887
You flirting with me. kid?

188
00:16:02.361 --> 00:16:05.297
Because. no offense.
but you ain't my type.

189
00:16:06.632 --> 00:16:09.568
And I'm not looking to get friendly
with the man who helped gut my boss.

190
00:16:12.405 --> 00:16:14.271
I'm sorry about Death.

191
00:16:15.508 --> 00:16:16.737
So am I.

192
00:16:18.077 --> 00:16:19.602
But people are
still dying. so...

193
00:16:20.613 --> 00:16:22.912
Work to do. Souls to collect.

194
00:16:24.250 --> 00:16:25.650
Messages to deliver.

195
00:16:27.954 --> 00:16:29.479
What kind of messages?

196
00:16:31.257 --> 00:16:32.281
It's over.

197
00:16:34.393 --> 00:16:35.417
What's over?

198
00:16:36.429 --> 00:16:37.692
You and Dean.

199
00:16:38.297 --> 00:16:42.132
Dying and coming
back. again and again.

200
00:16:44.136 --> 00:16:47.834
The old Death thought
it was funny. but now.

201
00:16:48.541 --> 00:16:51.101
there's one hard. fast
rule in this universe.

202
00:16:52.111 --> 00:16:54.945
What lives. dies.

203
00:16:56.449 --> 00:16:59.886
So. the next time you or
your brother bite it. well.

204
00:17:00.887 --> 00:17:02.321
you're not going to Heaven.

205
00:17:02.889 --> 00:17:03.889
Or Hell.

206
00:17:04.790 --> 00:17:07.851
One of us. and.
Lord. I hope it's me.

207
00:17:08.895 --> 00:17:11.797
we're gonna make a mistake.
and toss you out into the Empty.

208
00:17:15.568 --> 00:17:18.470
And nothing comes
back from that.

209
00:17:27.146 --> 00:17:28.614
I know you're dying.

210
00:17:30.950 --> 00:17:31.950
I can feel it.

211
00:17:34.120 --> 00:17:37.420
You're unclean. in
the biblical sense.

212
00:17:45.364 --> 00:17:47.230
So. I'll be seeing
you again. Sam.

213
00:17:49.201 --> 00:17:50.863
Seeing you real soon.

214
00:17:54.307 --> 00:17:55.832
Name's Billie. by the way.

215
00:17:59.812 --> 00:18:02.509
Again. Metatron. Where is he?

216
00:18:03.015 --> 00:18:04.506
I don't know.

217
00:18:04.817 --> 00:18:06.615
- But you broke him out of Heaven?
- Yes.

218
00:18:06.919 --> 00:18:09.718
- And took his grace?
- Yes.

219
00:18:09.989 --> 00:18:12.754
And you expect us to believe
he. what. just gave you the slip?

220
00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:14.993
No powers? No wings?

221
00:18:15.595 --> 00:18:17.086
Metatron tricked me.

222
00:18:17.730 --> 00:18:19.596
- So. you're just stupid.
- Or he's lying.

223
00:18:20.366 --> 00:18:22.699
- Or that.
- One way to find out.

224
00:18:26.238 --> 00:18:28.139
What should we cut off first?

225
00:18:32.211 --> 00:18:35.375
Eenie. meenie.

226
00:18:37.083 --> 00:18:38.083
miney.

227
00:18:41.921 --> 00:18:42.921
or mo?

228
00:18:54.266 --> 00:18:55.757
That's enough!

229
00:18:58.037 --> 00:18:59.061
Hannah?

230
00:19:00.773 --> 00:19:03.436
- What are you doing?
- Getting answers.

231
00:19:05.544 --> 00:19:08.241
No. This isn't how we do things.

232
00:19:09.782 --> 00:19:10.782
Get out.

233
00:19:14.854 --> 00:19:15.854
Out!

234
00:19:26.365 --> 00:19:27.697
Thank you.

235
00:19:28.834 --> 00:19:29.927
Don't thank me yet.

236
00:19:30.870 --> 00:19:33.965
Something's happened.
Castiel. Something horrible.

237
00:20:21.887 --> 00:20:22.887
So.

238
00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:26.415
I know it's been a long time.

239
00:20:31.697 --> 00:20:34.132
but Dean and I. we've
been through a lot of bad.

240
00:20:35.901 --> 00:20:37.460
But this is different.

241
00:20:38.838 --> 00:20:40.898
This is my fault and I
don't know how to fix it.

242
00:20:44.977 --> 00:20:47.469
And if I have to die. I've
made my peace with that. but.

243
00:20:50.349 --> 00:20:53.547
please. Dean deserves better.

244
00:20:59.358 --> 00:21:00.883
Dean deserves a life.

245
00:21:04.196 --> 00:21:06.756
There are people out
there. good people.

246
00:21:08.267 --> 00:21:12.102
who are going to
suffer because of me.

247
00:21:12.338 --> 00:21:15.502
And I am not asking
you to clean up my mess.

248
00:21:16.108 --> 00:21:18.270
Hell. I don't even
know if you're out there.

249
00:21:20.379 --> 00:21:22.541
but if you are.

250
00:21:23.482 --> 00:21:24.973
and if you can hear me.

251
00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:26.785
I. um...

252
00:21:28.487 --> 00:21:30.479
We need your help. God.

253
00:21:32.491 --> 00:21:33.857
We need to know there's hope.

254
00:21:35.761 --> 00:21:37.491
We need a sign.

255
00:22:10.262 --> 00:22:12.060
What does that mean?

256
00:22:20.739 --> 00:22:21.798
Hey.

257
00:22:22.975 --> 00:22:24.102
Where's the kid?

258
00:22:24.510 --> 00:22:25.944
We got another problem.

259
00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:27.369
Figures.

260
00:22:27.546 --> 00:22:28.741
I tried to stop her.

261
00:22:28.981 --> 00:22:31.712
but my grandma's real
Catholic. and after the crazy.

262
00:22:31.884 --> 00:22:35.082
she called her priest
who sent over an exorcist.

263
00:22:36.322 --> 00:22:38.154
- Really?
- Yeah.

264
00:22:51.837 --> 00:22:53.328
Hello. my son.

265
00:23:04.016 --> 00:23:06.042
- Crowley?
- Father Crowley.

266
00:23:07.620 --> 00:23:09.782
- Do you know each other?
<i>- Oh. yes.</i>

267
00:23:10.422 --> 00:23:13.119
Dean was a rather
scrumptious young altar boy.

268
00:23:17.863 --> 00:23:20.594
Can I talk to you
outside? Father.

269
00:23:22.134 --> 00:23:25.161
Of course. After
I finish my tea.

270
00:23:39.752 --> 00:23:40.752
No.

271
00:23:42.288 --> 00:23:43.449
This is safer.

272
00:23:55.067 --> 00:23:56.763
I wasn't lying about Metatron.

273
00:23:57.937 --> 00:23:59.064
I know.

274
00:24:00.172 --> 00:24:01.970
But right now I'm
more worried about you.

275
00:24:03.842 --> 00:24:05.003
Can you heal me?

276
00:24:13.052 --> 00:24:14.179
I can't.

277
00:24:15.087 --> 00:24:18.114
I'm sorry. This...
It's powerful magic.

278
00:24:21.060 --> 00:24:23.962
Really? Father Crowley? Really?

279
00:24:24.363 --> 00:24:26.832
I'm sorry. Agent
Pathetic-Has-Been-Rockstar.

280
00:24:27.166 --> 00:24:29.658
did I offend your
delicate sensibilities?

281
00:24:29.935 --> 00:24:31.164
<i>Where have you been?</i>

282
00:24:32.071 --> 00:24:34.950
Your brother. and that idiot angel. do
you know what they have been doing?

283
00:24:34.974 --> 00:24:36.340
- I've heard.
- Everything?

284
00:24:36.608 --> 00:24:38.270
Enough. What are you doing here?

285
00:24:38.944 --> 00:24:40.970
Same as you. I'm working a case.

286
00:24:42.314 --> 00:24:45.478
I feel the spell just
cutting deeper and deeper.

287
00:24:45.684 --> 00:24:47.846
And I'm trying to
fight it. I'm trying. but...

288
00:24:48.087 --> 00:24:51.023
Does it have anything to do with the
disturbance in Superior. Nebraska?

289
00:24:55.094 --> 00:24:56.289
You know about that?

290
00:24:56.895 --> 00:24:58.727
Alarms have been
sounding in Heaven. Castiel.

291
00:24:59.898 --> 00:25:02.834
Alarms that haven't
gone off in ever.

292
00:25:04.036 --> 00:25:05.436
We don't even know
what they mean.

293
00:25:06.772 --> 00:25:08.707
Those alarms are
for The Darkness.

294
00:25:15.481 --> 00:25:16.847
<i>The Darkness is a story.</i>

295
00:25:18.684 --> 00:25:20.744
<i>No. it's not. It's real.</i>

296
00:25:25.224 --> 00:25:26.624
The Darkness.

297
00:25:27.559 --> 00:25:30.085
it's been locked away
since the dawn of creation.

298
00:25:32.331 --> 00:25:33.890
<i>And now it's free.</i>

299
00:25:35.434 --> 00:25:37.266
Hey. Whatever's
wrong. Dean will fix it.

300
00:25:38.003 --> 00:25:39.027
God help us.

301
00:25:40.606 --> 00:25:42.074
I wouldn't count on that.

302
00:25:45.944 --> 00:25:47.276
It's okay.

303
00:25:50.616 --> 00:25:53.142
- Where is it?
- I don't know.

304
00:25:54.219 --> 00:25:56.654
Then who would? The Winchesters?

305
00:25:58.424 --> 00:26:02.885
Castiel. if this is true.
it's the end. For all of us.

306
00:26:04.329 --> 00:26:07.094
Sam and Dean. where are they?

307
00:26:08.767 --> 00:26:10.759
- I don't know.
- Then think harder!

308
00:26:13.305 --> 00:26:14.500
How did you find me?

309
00:26:15.340 --> 00:26:18.401
I have sources in
the Catholic Church.

310
00:26:18.677 --> 00:26:22.341
Nuns that owe me a favor.
Priests with a taste for...

311
00:26:22.681 --> 00:26:24.513
Okay. all right.
yeah. I can imagine.

312
00:26:26.218 --> 00:26:27.584
You really can't.

313
00:26:28.754 --> 00:26:31.383
Anyhow. they hear a demonic
possession. they call me.

314
00:26:31.757 --> 00:26:34.158
If it's one of mine. I
tell them to ignore it.

315
00:26:34.526 --> 00:26:36.620
If it's. say. a
demon gone rogue.

316
00:26:36.829 --> 00:26:39.697
well. that's when Father
Crowley comes out to play.

317
00:26:41.100 --> 00:26:42.693
So. you think there's
a demon in there?

318
00:26:43.402 --> 00:26:44.734
Not even a little bit.

319
00:27:03.622 --> 00:27:05.716
<i>- I saved you.</i>
- No.

320
00:27:06.358 --> 00:27:07.656
I don't think you did.

321
00:27:09.294 --> 00:27:14.232
I think that you told Efram
and Jonah to bring me here.

322
00:27:14.600 --> 00:27:17.263
and to hurt me and
so you arranged to...

323
00:27:19.771 --> 00:27:22.764
To burst in and save me.

324
00:27:23.876 --> 00:27:25.520
You were hoping that
I would be so grateful.

325
00:27:25.544 --> 00:27:27.877
that I would do
anything you said.

326
00:27:28.113 --> 00:27:31.572
That I would tell you anything
that you wanted to know.

327
00:27:38.090 --> 00:27:39.251
Why. Hannah?

328
00:27:40.859 --> 00:27:41.986
We were friends.

329
00:27:44.263 --> 00:27:46.061
That was before
you freed Metatron.

330
00:27:48.033 --> 00:27:49.262
Before...

331
00:27:51.470 --> 00:27:53.598
The other angels. they hate you.

332
00:27:54.306 --> 00:27:55.467
And what about you?

333
00:27:56.775 --> 00:27:57.834
Do you hate me?

334
00:28:01.246 --> 00:28:02.680
<i>Doesn't matter.</i>

335
00:28:05.851 --> 00:28:07.285
We took a vote.

336
00:28:07.586 --> 00:28:11.682
Democracy in action and
Hannah's doing the job.

337
00:28:14.660 --> 00:28:17.630
I won't give you Sam and Dean.

338
00:28:19.731 --> 00:28:20.731
Sure you will.

339
00:28:21.600 --> 00:28:23.193
We're gonna hack your brain.

340
00:28:30.075 --> 00:28:34.308
Whatever's in that house. I can
taste the power radiating from it.

341
00:28:36.048 --> 00:28:38.279
Oh. Jenna.

342
00:28:38.684 --> 00:28:40.016
You scared me.

343
00:28:40.552 --> 00:28:41.713
<i>That thing.</i>

344
00:28:43.589 --> 00:28:44.589
It's old.

345
00:28:44.790 --> 00:28:47.385
What'd you do? Drop
a bowling ball up there?

346
00:28:48.060 --> 00:28:49.060
Deep.

347
00:28:50.062 --> 00:28:51.223
Jenna?

348
00:28:56.201 --> 00:28:57.294
Dark.

349
00:28:58.003 --> 00:28:59.403
Honey. are you all right?

350
00:29:01.206 --> 00:29:02.606
I always wanted to try this.

351
00:29:11.750 --> 00:29:14.447
Jenna? Jenna.

352
00:29:20.259 --> 00:29:22.228
Well. hello. plot twist.

353
00:29:26.098 --> 00:29:27.361
Anything?

354
00:29:28.133 --> 00:29:30.728
- Not yet.
- You said you knew how to do this.

355
00:29:31.470 --> 00:29:34.030
I watched Naomi. Once.

356
00:29:36.508 --> 00:29:37.532
Enough.

357
00:29:38.110 --> 00:29:40.310
Look. you don't wanna get
your pretty hands dirty. fine.

358
00:29:40.479 --> 00:29:42.414
Walk away. But this
is happening. Gimme.

359
00:29:45.017 --> 00:29:47.987
Now hold still.
this one might hurt.

360
00:29:48.453 --> 00:29:49.512
I said stop.

361
00:29:50.989 --> 00:29:53.618
You get in my way again...

362
00:29:54.092 --> 00:29:57.221
You touch me again and I

363
00:29:58.930 --> 00:30:00.159
will

364
00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:03.632
end you!

365
00:30:03.902 --> 00:30:04.961
Uh. Efram...

366
00:30:22.220 --> 00:30:24.553
- Castiel...
- No!

367
00:31:00.459 --> 00:31:01.483
No.

368
00:31:06.431 --> 00:31:07.431
No.

369
00:31:31.723 --> 00:31:33.282
<i>Sam. Sam. Sam.</i>

370
00:31:35.994 --> 00:31:38.930
You're fine. You're fine.
You're fine. You're fine.

371
00:31:40.332 --> 00:31:43.928
You're unclean. in
the biblical sense.

372
00:32:37.489 --> 00:32:38.548
<i>Don't!</i>

373
00:32:39.157 --> 00:32:40.523
<i>Don't do this to yourself.</i>

374
00:32:40.725 --> 00:32:42.023
<i>Don't do this to yourself.</i>

375
00:32:43.195 --> 00:32:44.754
<i>Oh. God.</i>

376
00:32:46.565 --> 00:32:50.002
<i>Wait... Stop! I can't...</i>

377
00:32:50.602 --> 00:32:55.597
<i>Don't do this to
yourself. Wait. Stop!</i>

378
00:33:18.363 --> 00:33:20.127
Jen? Jenna?

379
00:33:20.765 --> 00:33:22.290
- Really?
- What?

380
00:33:23.034 --> 00:33:26.436
We have no idea what ancient.
world-shattering evil we're dealing with.

381
00:33:26.638 --> 00:33:28.038
but go right ahead.

382
00:33:28.440 --> 00:33:29.533
Let 'em know we're coming!

383
00:33:31.042 --> 00:33:33.602
Listen. Velma. this isn't
the Scooby Gang. okay?

384
00:33:33.945 --> 00:33:35.880
- So. either shut up. or get out.
- Easy. tiger.

385
00:33:36.281 --> 00:33:38.273
Just trying to help.

386
00:33:41.152 --> 00:33:42.518
I'm way more of a Daphne.

387
00:34:09.314 --> 00:34:11.112
We're bound. Dean.

388
00:34:12.517 --> 00:34:13.985
We'll always be bound.

389
00:34:14.486 --> 00:34:16.421
We will always help each other.

390
00:34:18.523 --> 00:34:19.923
The child likes you.

391
00:34:21.760 --> 00:34:24.924
<i>No surprise. really.
You're very maternal.</i>

392
00:34:32.537 --> 00:34:34.130
We gotta find Jenna.

393
00:35:51.816 --> 00:35:52.875
Hey.

394
00:35:54.586 --> 00:35:55.918
Thank you.

395
00:35:57.455 --> 00:35:59.083
Let's go save the rest of them.

396
00:36:03.795 --> 00:36:04.956
Drama.

397
00:36:16.441 --> 00:36:19.036
Jenna? What are you doing?

398
00:36:19.678 --> 00:36:21.476
My grandma
collected these things.

399
00:36:21.946 --> 00:36:23.881
But I always thought
they were so blah.

400
00:36:30.555 --> 00:36:33.423
Don't worry. she won't
care. I cut her throat.

401
00:36:35.193 --> 00:36:36.684
Why did you do that?

402
00:36:37.495 --> 00:36:39.464
Because this woman
doesn't have a soul.

403
00:36:43.635 --> 00:36:44.635
Fascinating.

404
00:36:45.170 --> 00:36:46.847
What are you talking about?
How's that even possible?

405
00:36:46.871 --> 00:36:49.773
Amara's hungry.
She's a growing girl.

406
00:36:58.583 --> 00:36:59.642
Jenna.

407
00:37:00.385 --> 00:37:01.478
Listen to me.

408
00:37:02.387 --> 00:37:06.518
Whatever's happened. whatever's
going on. we can fix it. okay?

409
00:37:06.991 --> 00:37:08.357
But I don't wanna be fixed.

410
00:37:12.664 --> 00:37:14.826
I like the new me. She's a ball.

411
00:37:15.366 --> 00:37:16.366
Just come with us. Okay?

412
00:37:23.441 --> 00:37:24.909
Enough! Stop!

413
00:37:45.096 --> 00:37:46.189
I was getting bored.

414
00:37:51.703 --> 00:37:52.830
You killed her.

415
00:37:53.605 --> 00:37:54.629
You're welcome.

416
00:37:55.106 --> 00:37:59.339
- Where are you going?
- To see the child that eats souls.

417
00:38:01.045 --> 00:38:02.377
You don't get
what that thing is.

418
00:38:03.314 --> 00:38:04.314
Enlighten me.

419
00:38:06.818 --> 00:38:08.719
Come on. darling.
Don't play coy.

420
00:38:12.590 --> 00:38:14.286
I think Amara's The Darkness.

421
00:38:15.293 --> 00:38:16.293
Interesting.

422
00:38:18.196 --> 00:38:20.995
So. what now? You kill her? You?

423
00:38:23.334 --> 00:38:25.200
- I don't have a choice.
- Please.

424
00:38:25.904 --> 00:38:28.384
Even if you could murder a baby.
you couldn't murder that baby.

425
00:38:28.740 --> 00:38:30.020
I saw the way you looked at her.

426
00:38:31.676 --> 00:38:34.339
Me. on the other hand.
it's not like it'd be my first.

427
00:38:34.679 --> 00:38:36.545
- Was that an offer?
- It's a promise.

428
00:38:36.948 --> 00:38:39.068
- Right after I'm done with her.
- Stay away from her.

429
00:38:43.621 --> 00:38:44.884
Oh. Dean.

430
00:38:45.490 --> 00:38:46.924
Adorable little Dean.

431
00:38:47.759 --> 00:38:51.355
I want that child.
And I get what I want.

432
00:38:52.864 --> 00:38:54.696
You and Sam don't understand.

433
00:38:55.366 --> 00:38:57.858
I'm not your bloody sidekick.

434
00:39:02.807 --> 00:39:04.241
We've had some good times.

435
00:39:05.910 --> 00:39:09.574
So. I'm gonna give you
one chance. just one.

436
00:39:10.248 --> 00:39:11.341
to walk out that door.

437
00:39:11.816 --> 00:39:15.014
Or I'm gonna take you
apart. atom by atom.

438
00:39:16.254 --> 00:39:18.120
Do you understand?

439
00:39:21.593 --> 00:39:22.617
Bastard!

440
00:40:12.577 --> 00:40:14.217
<i>All right. I still
don't understand.</i>

441
00:40:14.245 --> 00:40:17.943
I mean. I thought The Darkness
was a woman. not a child.

442
00:40:18.416 --> 00:40:19.509
Same here.

443
00:40:20.184 --> 00:40:24.815
I don't know. maybe whatever I
saw wasn't real. maybe it was a vision.

444
00:40:26.457 --> 00:40:27.516
- Vision?
<i>- Yeah.</i>

445
00:40:31.930 --> 00:40:32.930
Huh.

446
00:40:34.866 --> 00:40:37.097
- Weird.
- Yeah. weird with

447
00:40:37.702 --> 00:40:40.069
a weird cherry on the weird
top. We've got to get a maid.

448
00:40:42.540 --> 00:40:46.534
You know. one with a little
uniform. and really big...

449
00:41:06.164 --> 00:41:07.530
Help me.

450
00:41:28.386 --> 00:41:31.720
My. haven't you grown
into a sweet young thing?

451
00:41:39.731 --> 00:41:41.324
Want some candy. little girl?

452
00:42:25.209 --> 00:42:26.209
English -SDH
